.TH "drm_bridge_chain_mode_set" 9 "drm_bridge_chain_mode_set" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_bridge_chain_mode_set \- set proposed mode for all bridges in the encoder chain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_bridge_chain_mode_set
.BI "(struct drm_bridge *bridge "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
bridge control structure
.IP "mode" 12
desired mode to be set for the encoder chain
.IP "adjusted_mode" 12
updated mode that works for this encoder chain
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls \fIdrm_bridge_funcs.mode_set\fP op for all the bridges in the
encoder chain, starting from the first bridge to the last.
.SH "NOTE"
the bridge passed should be the one closest to the encoder
